In [17]:
 # Check for missing or infinite values in 'budget' and 'gross' columns
missing_values = df[['budget', 'gross']].isnull().values.any()
infinite_values = df[['budget', 'gross']].isin([np.inf, -np.inf]).values.any()

if missing_values or infinite_values:
    # Replace missing or infinite values with a suitable value or handle them as needed
    df[['budget', 'gross']] = df[['budget', 'gross']].fillna(0).replace([np.inf, -np.inf], 0)
  
 #change datatypes of columns

df['budget']= df['budget'].astype('int64')
df['gross'] = df['gross'].astype('int64')
